Percussion instruments</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Percussion instruments are made of resonant material and make sounds when they are struck or shaken. This category includes entries <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">7.4.1 Sistrum&lt;REALIA:7.4.1&gt;</a> through <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">7.4.5 Wooden clappers&lt;REALIA:7.4.5&gt;</a>. For convenience, we may also include the drums, entry <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">7.4.6 Drum, hand drum, frame drum&lt;REALIA:7.4.6&gt;</a> (see also <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">7.3.4 Bagpipe (kettledrum, large drum)&lt;REALIA:7.3.4&gt;</a>). In the case of drums, the sound is made by striking a stretched membrane, often of animal skin.</h2>\n</div>",
